MinetestBot BOT 22-Sep-18 03:01 PM
Install (Linux)
The recommended way to install Minetest on Linux is through your package manager. Note: the version shipped by default may be out of date. In which case, you can use a PPA (if applicable), or compiling may be a better option.
For Debian/Ubuntu-based Distributions:
Open a terminal and run these 3 commands:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:minetestdevs/stable sudo apt update sudo apt install minetest
For Arch Distributions:
Open a terminal and run this command:
sudo pacman -S minetest
Again, this will vary depending on your distribution.
Google is your friend. While slightly more involved, compiling works on any Linux distribution. See ;minetest compile linux for details.
